5 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY Section 3, Chapter 372, O.S.L.
6 2023 (27A O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 3-8-103), is amended to read as
7 follows:
8 Section 3-8-103. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
9 a revolving fund for the Oklahoma Conservation Commission to be
10 designated the "North Canadian Watershed Water Restoration Revolving
11 Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
12 year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
13 Conservation Commission from appropriations, federal grants or
14 funds, municipal contributions, private contributions, and any other
15 sources, including interest earned from the income in the fund, that
16 are designated for deposit to such fund or designated for duties
17 associated with harmful woody species removal from the North
18 Canadian Watershed watersheds throughout the state. All monies
19 accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated and may
20 be budgeted and expended by the Conservation Commission to perform
21 the duties imposed on the Commission by law. Expenditures from said
22 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
23 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
